Data Source Name: Data from database: Landmine Contamination Casualties and Clearance (LC3D)

Series Name: Anti-vehicle mines destroyed refers to the total number of anti-vehicle mines destroyed annually
Series Code: Anti-vehicle mines destroyed refers to the total number of anti-vehicle mines destroyed annually. Anti-vehicle mines are examples of Anti-Personnel Mines (APM) which are mines designed to be exploded by the presence, proximity or contact of a person and that will incapacitate, injure or kill one or more persons.

Series Name: Mine area cleared refers to total area cleared of mines and ERW to a predefined standard
Series Code: Mine area cleared refers to total area cleared of mines and ERW to a predefined standard. This involves the systematic clearance of all explosive hazards from a mined area to a specific depth (i.e. humanitarian standards)

Series Name: Non Anti-vehicle mines destroyed efers to the total number of non  anti-vehicle mines destroyed annually
Series Code: Non Anti-vehicle mines destroyed efers to the total number of non  anti-vehicle mines destroyed annually
